('1 Samuel', 21, 'kids', 1, 'When David fled from Saul, he came to a priest at Nob. What was the priest''s name?', 'Ahimelech', 'Abiathar', 'Eli', 'Phinehas', 'a', '1 Samuel 21:1 — "Then came David to Nob to Ahimelech the priest: and Ahimelech was afraid at the meeting of David."'),
('1 Samuel', 21, 'kids', 2, 'Because David had no ordinary food, Ahimelech gave him a special bread from the tabernacle. What was this bread called?', 'Shewbread', 'Manna', 'Firstfruits bread', 'Unleavened bread', 'a', '1 Samuel 21:6 — "So the priest gave him hallowed bread: for there was no bread there but the shewbread, that was taken from before the LORD."'),
('1 Samuel', 21, 'kids', 3, 'David ran away to the city of Gath and pretended to be crazy so the king would not hurt him. What was the king of Gath''s name?', 'Achish', 'Agag', 'Abimelech', 'Abner', 'a', '1 Samuel 21:10 — "And David arose, and fled that day for fear of Saul, and went to Achish the king of Gath."');
