('1 Samuel', 24, 'kids', 1, 'Saul went into a cave to rest, not knowing David and his men were hiding in the back. What did David secretly cut off from Saul?', 'The skirt of his robe', 'A lock of his hair', 'The tassel of his belt', 'The edge of his sandal strap', 'a', '1 Samuel 24:4 — "Then the men of David said unto him...Then David arose, and cut off the skirt of Saul''s robe privily."'),
('1 Samuel', 24, 'kids', 2, 'Even after cutting Saul''s robe, David felt sorry. Why did he say he should not harm Saul?', 'Because Saul was the LORD''s anointed king', 'Because Saul was Jonathan''s father', 'Because Saul had once been kind to David', 'Because the law of Moses forbade harming elders', 'a', '1 Samuel 24:6 — "And he said unto his men, The LORD forbid that I should do this thing unto my master, the LORD''s anointed, to stretch forth mine hand against him, seeing he is the anointed of the LORD."'),
('1 Samuel', 24, 'kids', 3, 'What did David call out to Saul after Saul left the cave, to show he meant no harm?', '"My lord the king"', '"O king, live forever"', '"Peace be unto thee, O Saul"', '"The LORD bless thee, my master"', 'a', '1 Samuel 24:8 — "David also arose afterward, and went out of the cave, and cried after Saul, saying, My lord the king. And when Saul looked behind him, David stooped with his face to the earth, and bowed himself."');
