('1 Samuel', 25, 'kids', 2, 'Nabal was a very rich man who refused to help David and his men even though David had protected his shepherds. What was his wife''s name, and what was she like?', 'Her name was Abigail and she was a woman of good understanding and beautiful', 'Her name was Merab and she was a brave and strong woman', 'Her name was Rizpah and she was a faithful and patient woman', 'Her name was Michal and she was a clever and cunning woman', 'a', '1 Samuel 25:3 — "Now the name of the man was Nabal; and the name of his wife Abigail: and she was a woman of good understanding, and of a beautiful countenance."'),
