('1 Samuel', 26, 'kids', 2, 'Why was no one in Saul''s camp awake when David crept in?', 'The LORD had caused a deep sleep to fall upon them all', 'It was past midnight and they had feasted heavily', 'David''s men had put something in their water', 'A heavy fog had confused the sentries', 'a', '1 Samuel 26:12 — "they were all asleep; for a deep sleep from the LORD was fallen upon them."'),
