('1 Samuel', 29, 'kids', 1, 'When the Philistine army gathered to fight Israel, David and his men were marching with Achish. What did the other Philistine lords say about David being there?', 'They did not want David to fight with them because he might turn against them in battle', 'They were happy to have David because he was a great warrior on their side', 'They asked David to lead the front line of the battle', 'They wanted David to guard the camp while the Philistines fought', 'a', '1 Samuel 29:4 — "And the princes of the Philistines were wroth with him; and the princes of the Philistines said unto him, Make this fellow return, that he may go again to his place which thou hast appointed him, and let him not go down with us to battle, lest in the battle he be an adversary to us."'),
('1 Samuel', 29, 'kids', 2, 'What did Achish tell David when he sent him away from the battle?', 'That David had been good and upright but the other lords did not want him there, so he must return home to Ziklag', 'That David was being punished for raiding the wrong villages', 'That David had been discovered as a spy for Israel', 'That Achish needed David to protect Gath while the army was away', 'a', '1 Samuel 29:6 — "Then Achish called David, and said unto him, Surely, as the LORD liveth, thou hast been upright, and thy going out and thy coming in with me in the host is good in my sight: for I have not found evil in thee since the day of thy coming unto me."'),
('1 Samuel', 29, 'kids', 3, 'Where did David and his men go after being sent away from the Philistine army?', 'They returned to Ziklag', 'They returned to the cave of Adullam', 'They went to the wilderness of Engedi', 'They traveled to Hebron in Judah', 'a', '1 Samuel 29:11 — "So David and his men rose up early to depart in the morning, to return into the land of the Philistines. And the Philistines went up to Jezreel."');
