('1 Samuel', 30, 'kids', 1, 'When David and his men returned to Ziklag they found terrible news. What had happened to the town while they were away?', 'The Amalekites had burned it and taken all the women and children captive', 'The Philistines had destroyed it as punishment for David leaving the army', 'The men of Judah had attacked it thinking David was a traitor', 'A great storm had swept through and destroyed all the houses', 'a', '1 Samuel 30:1-2 — "the Amalekites had invaded the south, and Ziklag, and smitten Ziklag, and burned it with fire; And had taken the women captives, that were therein: they slew not any, either great or small, but carried them away."'),
('1 Samuel', 30, 'kids', 2, 'David and his men were so sad they wept until they had no more tears. David''s own men were so angry they talked about stoning him. What did David do to feel better and find courage?', 'He encouraged himself in the LORD his God', 'He fasted and prayed for three days', 'He called for the prophet Gad to comfort him', 'He read from the scrolls of Moses', 'a', '1 Samuel 30:6 — "but David encouraged himself in the LORD his God."'),
('1 Samuel', 30, 'kids', 3, 'God told David to go after the Amalekites and promised he would recover all that had been taken. Did David get everything back?', 'Yes, David recovered all and nothing was missing, neither small nor great', 'David got back most of the people but some of the cattle were lost', 'David rescued the women and children but the city of Ziklag remained burned', 'David recovered everything except the silver and gold which the Amalekites had already sold', 'a', '1 Samuel 30:19 — "And there was nothing lacking to them, neither small nor great, neither sons nor daughters, neither spoil, nor any thing that they had taken to them: David recovered all."');
