('1 Samuel', 31, 'kids', 1, 'In the great battle at Gilboa, Saul''s sons were killed. Which of his sons is mentioned by name as dying in that battle?', 'Jonathan, Abinadab, and Melchi-shua', 'Ish-bosheth, Amnon, and Absalom', 'Mephibosheth, Jonadab, and Shimei', 'Michal, Merab, and Rizpah', 'a', '1 Samuel 31:2 — "And the Philistines followed hard upon Saul and upon his sons; and the Philistines slew Jonathan, and Abinadab, and Malchishua, Saul''s sons."'),
('1 Samuel', 31, 'kids', 2, 'Saul was badly wounded by arrows. He asked his armourbearer to kill him so the Philistines could not capture him. What did the armourbearer do?', 'He was too afraid to do it, so Saul fell on his own sword', 'He killed Saul as asked and then ran away', 'He carried Saul off the battlefield to safety', 'He tried to treat Saul''s wounds and refused to kill him', 'a', '1 Samuel 31:4-5 — "Therefore Saul took a sword, and fell upon it...And when his armourbearer saw that Saul was dead, he fell likewise upon his sword, and died with him."'),
('1 Samuel', 31, 'kids', 3, 'The brave men of the city of Jabesh-gilead showed respect for Saul and his sons. What kind thing did they do for Saul''s body?', 'They traveled all night, took the bodies down from the wall of Beth-shan, and gave them a proper burial', 'They built a great monument on the battlefield of Gilboa', 'They brought the bodies to Jerusalem for a royal funeral', 'They carried the bones to the cave of Adullam where David''s men kept guard', 'a', '1 Samuel 31:11-13 — "And when the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead heard of that which the Philistines had done to Saul; All the valiant men arose, and went all night, and took the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth-shan...and buried them under a tree at Jabesh, and fasted seven days."');
